There was tension on Thursday at Aye-Ekiti in Oye Local Government Area of Ekiti State, as two persons were killed in an accident involving a vehicle driven by a university student. The Nation gathered that the accident occurred about 2:30pm when a vehicle lost control and hit two persons on the Ayegbaju-Ifaki Ekiti Road. An eyewitness said the accident was caused by recklessness on the part of the driver, who was speeding before skidding off the road to crush the victims, who were on a motorcycle, to death. He said the driver fled the scene for fear of being lynched by youths, before he voluntarily reported himself at the nearest police station. Police spokesman Sunday Abutu, who confirmed the death of the victims, said the driver had been detained at the command headquarters in Ado-Ekiti.